		<div>Vexo,<br />
<br />
The fault with instants was not instants, it was what was arount them. We simply had nothing else to use. So we used only instants.<br />
When WMS was fixed we were exited like WMS is such a great nuke and all of us used it extensively. Truth be told WMS is not such a great nuke but compared to what else was there it was light years away.<br />
It does not take great imagination to make wizards a very exciting and effective class with predifined goals. We are burst DPS, we ought to be called to unload large amount of dmg in a short timeframe. Instants are ideal for this and there is no reason to kill them. You just need to build around them.<br />
What bugs me the most is the arguments against instants, most notably how they scale too far. Wizards in fact have tools to scale damage over 1 to 2 min timeframe better than any class in game. Hello, thats exactly how it should be, we are supposed to be able to do that. What is the problem. What logic in saying we should not be ahead in 2 min parses over any class. in a 5 min fight most high DPS classes are ahead of us. We do not cry about that.<br />
Prathun is a wierdo. He has no clue what he wants. He does things at the whim. He has it in for us since April. Even though situation is totaly different today he is nerfing us as if it was April 2007.<br />
There are things to like in SoF on the spell side. Hey if you take a nuke and make it cast in half the time that can only be good. WMC and CI have 0.75 sec cast time, got to love that. Problem is, you now have some of what we should have had in TSS but you don't have instants. That's no good.<br />
He simply cannot see what the freaking game is all about from a perspective of the player. Why do I have too trade nukes this way. Why don't you fucking make me happy and give me both. If you think DPS is too high lets cut the numbres down to size. There is no reason you should make me chain instants only or not be able to chain them at all. There is a very simple way to find middle ground.</div>
	</td>
